n","default":false,"description":"If a project has no sObject definitions, specifies whether to automatically refresh sObject definitions on extension activation (true) or not (false)."},"salesforcedx-vscode-core.NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS":{"type":"string","default":null,"description":"NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS CLI environment variable value"},"salesforcedx-vscode-core.SF_LOG_LEVEL":{"type":"string","enum":["trace","debug","info","warn","error","fatal"],"default":"fatal","description":"SF_LOG_LEVEL CLI environment variable value"},"salesforcedx-vscode-core.telemetry-tag":{"type":"string","default":null,"description":"Specifies the tag to include in telemetry data sent to Salesforce."}}},"jsonValidation":[{"fileMatch":"sfdx-project.json","url":"./resources/schemas/sfdx-project.schema.json"},{"fileMatch":"*-scratch-def.json","url":"./resources/schemas/project-scratch-def.schema.json"}],"languages":[{"id":"ignore","filenames":[".forceignore"]},{"id":"json","filenamePatterns":["*.wdash","*.wdf","*.wdpr","*.wlens","*.orchestration"]},{"id":"forcesourcemanifest","aliases":["ForceSourceManifest","forcesourcemanifest"],"filenamePatterns":["**/manifest/**/*.xml"]}],"grammars":[{"language":"forcesourcemanifest","scopeName":"manifest.text.xml","path":"./syntaxes/manifestXML.tmLanguage.json"}],"walkthroughs":[{"id":"sf.connected-org","title":"Connected Org","description":"Connect to and manage your Salesforce orgs. Learn about default org concepts and management.","steps":[{"id":"understand-default-org","title":"Understanding Your Default Org","description":"Salesforce Extensions runs commands against your **default org**. The type of org depends on your development model:\n\n• **Package development model** - Typically a scratch org for isolated development\n• **Org development model** - Usually a sandbox, Developer Edition (DE) org, or Trailhead Playground\n\nYour default org is displayed in the VS Code footer and determines where your commands execute.\n\n*Learn more: [Default Org Documentation](https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/platform/sfvscode-extensions/guide/default-org.html)*","media":{"image":"images/walkthrough/org-picker.png","altText":"default org concept"}},{"id":"set-default-org","title":"Set or Change Your Default Org","description":"To set or change the org you're developing against:\n\n**Using VS Code Activity Bar:**\n1. Click the **org alias** or **plug icon**\n2. Select a different org or choose **SFDX: Set a Default Org** to authorize a new org\n\n**Using Command Palette:**\n1. **SFDX: Authorize an Org** - Connect to an existing org, or\n2. **SFDX: Create a Default Scratch Org** - Create a new scratch org, or\n3. **SFDX: Set a Default Org**\n\n[Set Default Org](command:sf.set.default.org)","media":{"image":"images/walkthrough/org-picker.png","altText":"changing default org"},"completionEvents":["onCommand:sf.set.default.org"]},{"id":"open-default-org","title":"Open and Manage Your Default Org","description":"Once you have a default org set, you can easily access it:\n\n**Open your default org:**\n1. Click the open org icon next to the default org icon in the footer, or\n2. Use Command Palette: **SFDX: Open Default Org**\n\n**Manage your org:**\nTo manage your default org, you can:\n1. **SFDX: Log Out from Default Org**\n2. **SFDX: Display Org Details for Default Org**\n\nOpening your org launches it in your default browser for easy access to the Salesforce interface.","media":{"image":"images/walkthrough/org-picker.png","altText":"opening and managing org"}}]}]}},"location":{"$mid":1,"path":"/c:/Users/89961/.vscode/extensions/salesforce.salesforcedx-vscode-core-66.5.2","scheme":"file"},"isBuiltin":false,"targetPlatform":"undefined","publisherDisplayName":"Salesforce","metadata":{"isApplicationScoped":false,"isMachineScoped":false,"isBuiltin":false,"installedTimestamp":1775797119763,"pinned":false,"source":"gallery","id":"1d9d0701-6f65-4174-a1a6-5720ffa59b61","publisherId":"656b996d-3c70-47b4-937e-e77c013faeea","publisherDispla